// Signing.xcconfig — code-signing configuration for ConnectBareWorkflowDemo.
//
// Why this file exists
// --------------------
// Mobile push requires the app to build with an Apple Developer *team* so the
// `aps-environment` entitlement is materialised into the signed (or, on the
// Simulator, the "simulated") entitlements. Without a team the OS returns NO
// APNs token — and on the Simulator it fails *silently* (no error, no token).
//
// Xcode's GUI injects your team automatically via "Automatically manage
// signing", which is why push works when you Run from Xcode. Command-line
// builds (`npm run ios`, `xcodebuild`, CI) do NOT auto-pick a team, so the
// entitlement is dropped and registration never produces a token.
//
// This config is referenced as the *project-level* base configuration (set by
// scripts/configure_signing.rb), so it applies to the app and both push
// extensions, and survives `pod install` (CocoaPods only owns the per-target
// base configs). It optionally includes a gitignored local override below.
//
// To enable CLI push testing
// ---------------------------
//   cp Signing.local.example.xcconfig Signing.local.xcconfig
//   # edit Signing.local.xcconfig and set DEVELOPMENT_TEAM to your Team ID
//
// The committed sample stays team-free; each developer sets their own team
// locally. The `?` makes the include optional — a fresh clone without the
// local file still builds (only push registration is unavailable until set).
#include? "Signing.local.xcconfig"
